{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-blogs-blog-detail-js","path":"/blog/how-to-get-your-alexa-skill-ready-by-kotlin","result":{"pageContext":{"post":{"id":"5f313450-9c3b-5aba-9855-5a27323cb1dc","title":"How to get your Alexa skill ready by Kotlin","excerpt":"Learn how to create an Alexa skill using the Google backed Kotlin language","_rawBody":[{"_key":"c1a62146ecf1","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"c1a62146ecf10","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Alexa, Ask myweather What is the weather here today. ⛅"}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"39e73bf1960a","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"39e73bf1960a0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Hola folks 👋, from the title you might have got an idea about what we will be discussing here. Adding more to it, here we will take a deep dive to know how we can be able to integrate simple Alexa skill using Kotlin. And for that, we will use weather API."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"58eecdcb46fc","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"58eecdcb46fc0","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"To create simple AWS lambda function make sure you full fill following requirements."}],"markDefs":[],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"d295f7aa06e8","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"d295f7aa06e80","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"An account in the "},{"_key":"d295f7aa06e81","_type":"span","marks":["25a274d1fc48"],"text":"Amazon developer console"},{"_key":"d295f7aa06e82","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"."}],"level":1,"listItem":"number","markDefs":[{"_key":"25a274d1fc48","_type":"link","href":"https://developer.amazon.com/"}],"style":"normal"},{"_key":"e66268190782","_type":"block","children":[{"_key":"e662681907820","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":"Kotlin supported integrated development environment ( I personally like "},{"_key":"e662681907821","_type":"span","marks":["bd91cd63693e"],"text":"Intelij Idea"},{"_key":"e662681907822","_type":"span","marks":[],"text":" from Jet brains)."}],"level":1,"listItem":"number"